    "In another study, Arnold et al. (2020) reported that suggestive keyboard technologies affect the writers' choices who often follow AI-based text suggestions, while it improves their writing speed.",
    "Jakesch et al. (2023) reported that when suggestive keyboards were used, in which an LLM was fine-tuned to suggest positive (negative) phrases, users were likely to write positive (negative) opinions.",
    "In the field of information retrieval (IR), several researchers have investigated systems for searching information to support decision-making.",
    "Rinott et al. (2015) proposed a method to search for evidence supporting a given claim from unstructured documents.",
    "Liu et al. (2022) proposed CRYSTALLINE, a browser developed to tabulate collected Web information for efficient decision-making."
